cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI

This paper proposes a method for improving the efficiency of Sparse-Group Lasso (SGL) and nonnegative Lasso, which are commonly used regression techniques in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also includes experiments on real data sets, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
